{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KqKLgHFeADqHYqkg5P4qaw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I have the complete file. Here are the key sections you requested:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **`settleRound()` Function — Full Implementation**\n**Lines 344–502**\n\nThe function:\n- Checks if the candle has closed (line 351–359)\n- Counts green/red entries (lines 361–363)\n- Fetches treasury and close price from Hermes (lines 366–378)\n- Determines outcome: refund vs. green win vs. red win (lines 386–392)\n- Builds and sends on-chain settle instruction (lines 406–425)\n- Persists settlement to DB (lines 441–487)\n\n---\n\n## 2. **DB Update Section — Lines 443–487**\n\n**Round record upsert (lines 443–455):**\n```typescript\nawait sql`\n  INSERT INTO closecall_rounds (round_id, pda, server_key, open_price, open_price_expo, phase, created_at)\n  VALUES (\n    ${String(Number(minuteTs))},\n    ${roundPda.toBase58()},\n    ${serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58()},\n    ${Number(round.openPrice)},\n    ${round.openPriceExpo},\n    'open',\n    NOW()\n  )\n  ON CONFLICT (round_id) DO NOTHING\n`;\n```\n\n**Settlement update (lines 474–487):**\n```typescript\nawait sql`\n  UPDATE closecall_rounds SET\n    phase = ${isRefund ? \"refunded\" : \"settled\"},\n    outcome = ${outcomeStr},\n    close_price = ${Number(hermesPrice.price)},\n    green_pool = ${Number(round.greenPool)},\n    red_pool = ${Number(round.redPool)},\n    total_fee = ${computedFee},\n    green_entries = ${sql.json(greenEntries)},\n    red_entries = ${sql.json(redEntries)},\n    settle_tx = ${sig},\n    settled_at = NOW()\n  WHERE round_id = ${String(Number(minuteTs))}\n`;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Structure of `green_entries` and `red_entries` — Lines 458–465**\n\n```typescript\nconst greenEntries = round.greenEntries.map((e) => ({\n  player: e.player.toBase58(),\n  amountLamports: Number(e.amountLamports),\n}));\nconst redEntries = round.redEntries.map((e) => ({\n  player: e.player.toBase58(),\n  amountLamports: Number(e.amountLamports),\n}));\n```\n\n**Entry shape:**\n- `player`: string (Solana address base58)\n- `amountLamports`: number (individual bet amount in lamports)\n\n---\n\n## 4. **Refund Logic — Lines 388–392**\n\n```typescript\nconst isRefund =\n  totalCount === 0 ||           // no entries at all\n  !hasBothSides ||              // all entries on one side\n  totalCount === 1 ||           // only one entry\n  hermesPrice.price === round.openPrice;  // price unchanged\n```\n\nWhen `isRefund` is true (line 395–399), all players from both sides are included in `remainingAccounts` to receive refunds.\n\n---\n\n## 5. **Payout Computation — Lines 469–471**\n\n```typescript\nconst totalPool = Number(round.greenPool) + Number(round.redPool);\nconst computedFee = isRefund ? 0 : Math.floor(totalPool * 300 / 10_000);\n```\n\n- **Fee**: 3% (300 bps) of total pool, truncated to integer lamports\n- **For refunds**: fee is 0\n- **Payout logic**: Computed off-chain here (on-chain settle instruction handles actual distribution to winners)\n\n---\n\n## 6. **round_id Field — Lines 446, 486**\n\n```typescript\nround_id = ${String(Number(minuteTs))}\n```\n\n- **Type**: string representation of a number\n- **Value**: the `minuteTs` (minute timestamp in seconds) converted to number then to string\n- **Used as**: PRIMARY KEY in `closecall_rounds` table\n- **Relationship to match_id**: The `minuteTs` is the minute boundary when the round opened; it doubles as the unique identifier persisted to the DB\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **Entries BEFORE settlement**: `round.greenEntries` and `round.redEntries` come from the on-chain account (decoded at line 313)\n2. **Pool values**: `round.greenPool` and `round.redPool` are summed from all entries in each side before settlement\n3. **Treasury**: Fetched fresh from on-chain config (line 367)\n4. **Price sources**: `round.openPrice` (stored on-chain at round creation), `hermesPrice.price` (fetched fresh at settlement time)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a706fbf8c5953ef1d (use SendMessage with to: 'a706fbf8c5953ef1d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40206\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 14934</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ab61bc6-f37e-46f2-adbe-0242ac985946","uuid":"13e71c9d-2b1b-46d3-bb1d-13494d66158e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:51:10.755Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The `settleRound()` function - its full implementation\n2. Where the DB update happens (around line 443-487)\n3. The structure of `green_entries` and `red_entries` (how entries look - fields like player, amountLamports)\n4. How refund logic works (isRefund detection)\n5. How payout is computed for winners\n6. The round_id field used as match_id\n\nReturn the relevant code sections with line numbers.","agentId":"a706fbf8c5953ef1d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I have the complete file. Here are the key sections you requested:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **`settleRound()` Function — Full Implementation**\n**Lines 344–502**\n\nThe function:\n- Checks if the candle has closed (line 351–359)\n- Counts green/red entries (lines 361–363)\n- Fetches treasury and close price from Hermes (lines 366–378)\n- Determines outcome: refund vs. green win vs. red win (lines 386–392)\n- Builds and sends on-chain settle instruction (lines 406–425)\n- Persists settlement to DB (lines 441–487)\n\n---\n\n## 2. **DB Update Section — Lines 443–487**\n\n**Round record upsert (lines 443–455):**\n```typescript\nawait sql`\n  INSERT INTO closecall_rounds (round_id, pda, server_key, open_price, open_price_expo, phase, created_at)\n  VALUES (\n    ${String(Number(minuteTs))},\n    ${roundPda.toBase58()},\n    ${serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58()},\n    ${Number(round.openPrice)},\n    ${round.openPriceExpo},\n    'op