{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NNzSvg6Dm9Fg42UNHGx6QU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the results:\n\n## Function Signature and Types\n\n### Type Definitions (lines 104-124 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\nexport type UserTransactionEvent = \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n\nexport interface UserTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  match_id: string;\n  event: UserTransactionEvent;\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  tx_sig: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface InsertUserTransactionParams {\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  event: UserTransactionEvent;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  txSig?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n### Function Signature (lines 245-246 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\n/** Insert a user transaction. Uses ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING for idempotency. */\ninsertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n```\n\n### Implementation (lines 533-546 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\nasync insertUserTransaction(params) {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO user_transactions (wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.wallet},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.event},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.txSig ?? null}\n    )\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n},\n```\n\n## Usage Patterns in settle-tx.ts\n\n### Coinflip Pattern (lines 304-323):\nTwo concurrent inserts — one for winner (event=\"win\") and one for loser (event=\"loss\"):\n\n```typescript\n// Write user transactions — win + loss\nconst loser = winner.equals(creator) ? opponent : creator;\nawait Promise.all([\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: loser.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"loss\",\n    amountLamports: Number(entryAmount),\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n]);\n```\n\n### Lord of RNGs Pattern (lines 518-543):\nOne insert for winner, then loop over all losing entries:\n\n```typescript\n// Write user transactions — win for winner, loss for each losing entry\nconst userTxInserts = [\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"lord\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n];\nfor (const entry of roundData.entries) {\n  if (!entry.player.equals(winner)) {\n    userTxInserts.push(\n      db.insertUserTransaction({\n        wallet: entry.player.toBase58(),\n        game: \"lord\",\n        matchId: round.match_id,\n        event: \"loss\",\n        amountLamports: Number(entry.amountLamports),\n        txSig: txSignature,\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n}\nawait Promise.all(userTxInserts);\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Both games pass `txSig` (the settlement transaction signature) for audit trail\n- Coinflip: winner gets `payoutAmount` (pool minus fees), loser gets their original `entryAmount`\n- Lord: winner gets `payoutAmount`, each loser gets their individual entry amount\n- Both use `Promise.all()` for concurrent inserts\n- The function is idempotent due to `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` clause"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2def4b501b9bbda (use SendMessage with to: 'ad2def4b501b9bbda' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51719\ntool_uses: 3\nduration_ms: 13646</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ab61bc6-f37e-46f2-adbe-0242ac985946","uuid":"d748a2b5-d8b4-4583-b7c1-76178b63a1ff","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:51:11.666Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` and find the `insertUserTransaction` function and its types (`InsertUserTransactionParams`, `UserTransactionEvent`). Show me the exact function signature and types. Also check how it's called in `settle-tx.ts` for the coinflip and lord patterns (look for `insertUserTransaction` calls). Return the relevant code with line numbers.","agentId":"ad2def4b501b9bbda","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the results:\n\n## Function Signature and Types\n\n### Type Definitions (lines 104-124 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\nexport type UserTransactionEvent = \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n\nexport interface UserTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  match_id: string;\n  event: UserTransactionEvent;\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  tx_sig: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface InsertUserTransactionParams {\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  event: UserTransactionEvent;\n  amountLamports: number;\n  txSig?: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n### Function Signature (lines 245-246 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\n/** Insert a user transaction. Uses ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING for idempotency. */\ninsertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n```\n\n### Implementation (lines 533-546 in db.ts):\n\n```typescript\nasync insertUserTransaction(params) {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO user_transactions (wallet, game, match_id, event, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (\n      ${params.wallet},\n      ${params.game},\n      ${params.matchId},\n      ${params.event},\n      ${params.amountLamports},\n      ${params.txSig ?? null}\n    )\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n},\n```\n\n## Usage Patterns in settle-tx.ts\n\n### Coinflip Pattern (lines 304-323):\nTwo concurrent inserts — one for winner (event=\"win\") and one for loser (event=\"loss\"):\n\n```typescript\n// Write user transactions — win + loss\nconst loser = winner.equals(creator) ? opponent : creator;\nawait Promise.all([\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: loser.toBase58(),\n    game: \"coinflip\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"loss\",\n    amountLamports: Number(entryAmount),\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n]);\n```\n\n### Lord of RNGs Pattern (lines 518-543):\nOne insert for winner, then loop over all losing entries:\n\n```typescript\n// Write user transactions — win for winner, loss for each losing entry\nconst userTxInserts = [\n  db.insertUserTransaction({\n    wallet: winner.toBase58(),\n    game: \"lord\",\n    matchId: round.match_id,\n    event: \"win\",\n    amountLamports: payoutAmount,\n    txSig: txSignature,\n  }),\n];\nfor (const entry of roundData.entries) {\n  if (!entry.player.equals(winner)) {\n    userTxInserts.push(\n      db.insertUserTransaction({\n        wallet: entry.player.toBase58(),\n        game: \"lord\",\n        matchId: round.match_id,\n        event: \"loss\",\n        amountLamports: Number(entry.amountLamports),\n        txSig: txSignature,\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n}\nawait Promise.all(userTxInserts);\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Both games pass `txSig` (the settlement transaction signature) for audit trail\n- Coinflip: winner gets `payoutAmount` (pool minus fees), loser gets their original `entryAmount`\n- Lord: winner gets `payoutAmount`, each loser gets their individual entry amount\n- Both use `Promise.all()` for concurrent inserts\n- The function is idempotent due to `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` clause"}],"totalDurationMs":13646,"totalTokens":51719,"totalToolUseCount":3,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11506,"cache_read_input_tokens":39218,"output_tokens":990,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"epheme